ACT:
 Allowing deduction under section 10(2) (xv) of the Income Tax Act-Revenue expenditure and Capital expenditure- Member of the Jute Mill Association entering into a working time agreement restricting the number of working hours per week for which the mills shall be entitled to work their looms, and also providing for transfer of such working hours between one mill and another amongst a particular group of Mills-Transfer styled as sale of loom hours-Whether the purchase revenue expenditure or capital expenditure for the purposes of Section 10(2) (xv) of the Act.
 
